description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are happy to announce that we have adevelopment Band 5 post in our Adult Community Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note we are happy to consider applications from current Band 4&#39;s undertaking the accelerated nursing programme and nursing students coming up to graduation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Community Adult Mental Health Team is based in Newmarket Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;and are looking to recruit passionate and good-humoured registered Nurses to work as part of our dynamic and supportive multi-disciplinary community team. We are proud of our proven track record of supporting and developing our colleagues both experienced and newly qualified to fulfil their career potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are especially looking to develop Band 5 nurses on their career path to a Band 6 by putting an excellent development plan in place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for staff who are committed to deliver an effective medical and therapeutic intervention to our Service User.We are in search for the colleagues who believing in the recovery principles, therapeutically minded in their approaches and place the needs of the Service User at the heart of the care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be able to display skills in flexible communication and want to go the extra mile for our Service Users who are under their treatment pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work alongside and be part of the multidisciplinary team and act as a spokesperson and intermediary for the Service User to ensure their voice is heard and that they receive the best quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to join our services as we have been having very different conversations with our stakeholders on how services should be delivered throughout West Suffolk. We are undergoing a transformation that sees us adapting to the ever-changing needs of local communities. We serve with new partnerships created within the voluntary care sector and primary care services. There is a collaborative excitement and optimism to engage in a transformational agenda that ensures and promotes positive health and wellbeing within communities and immediate localities. To update and join in the discussions please search for #averydifferentconversation  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Benefits:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits included with this role are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free car parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a comprehensive in house &amp; external training programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;career progression&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;starting annual leave of 27 days per annum increasing to 33 days pa based on length of service (plus paid bank holidays)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;staff physiotherapy service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;gym membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts and many more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To find out more about the job role click the job description, then click APPLY to start your candidate experience today.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please find attached our Job Description and Person Specification for more detail on your Key Accountabilities, then if you feel you have what it takes to make a difference in your local communities, click APPLY!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Interviews are to be confirmed, candidates may only be given a minimum of 3 days’ notice, please note this date is provisional and may be subject to change. You will be contacted via email and invited to book a time. These emails may go to your SPAM, so please keep checking all your emails if applying.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please visit our Facebook and Twitter page @NSFTjobs&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Karen Dawson - Clinical Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01638 558650, Email: karen.dawson@nsft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;James Nilsen-Clarke - Community Services Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mobile: 07795 847242, E: james.nilsen-clarke@nsft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
